Resource placement is stored in game_config.res_dists, one line per resource. Each line has a name, a resource-level weight, and up to four placement quadruplets. Top-level fields are colon-separated. Each quadruplet is parenthesized and comma-separated inside: terrain, climate, overlay, quad weight.

Example (Iron — global weight 4, two quads):

Iron : 4 : (TERR_HILLS, ALL_CLIMATES, ALL_OVERLAYS, 1) : (TERR_MOUNTAINS, ALL_CLIMATES, ALL_OVERLAYS, 2)

Example (Furs — global weight 1, two quads):

Furs : 1 : (TERR_PLAINS, CLIMATE_GRASSLAND, OVERLAY_FORESTS, 1) : (TERR_HILLS, CLIMATE_GRASSLAND, OVERLAY_FORESTS, 1)

The resource-level weight sets relative abundance across resources. Quad weights set relative frequency among quads for the same resource.

Terrain tokens:
 - ALL_TERRAINS
 - TERR_OCEAN
 - TERR_SEA
 - TERR_COASTAL
 - TERR_PLAINS
 - TERR_HILLS
 - TERR_MOUNTAINS

Climate tokens:
 - ALL_CLIMATES
 - CLIMATE_TUNDRA
 - CLIMATE_GRASSLAND
 - CLIMATE_PLAINS
 - CLIMATE_DESERT

Overlay tokens:
 - ALL_OVERLAYS
 - NO_OVERLAYS
 - OVERLAY_SWAMPS
 - OVERLAY_FORESTS
 - OVERLAY_JUNGLES
 - OVERLAY_RIVERS

Parsed into ResPlacement / ResQuad in static_state/res_placement.h via DataParserBase::parse_res_placement and ResDistParser.
